I find having to use the foreground script command to change to custom colours a nuisance, because I can't do it in-line.  I think a cool feature would be the following:

colour &lt;c1; 5090FF&gt;
colour &lt;c2; 5010FF&gt;
...
colour &lt;c9; 2090FF&gt;

Then:

msg &lt;|c1This is text in the first colour.  |c2This is text in the second colour. ... |c9This is text in the ninth color.&gt;
